This paper deals with the problem of estimating the location of a point source in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also investigates the performance of a localization algorithm, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel performance measure, which could be related to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
